API Integration Guide for Frontend people 

1. Signup Page (signup.html)

Button: Submit

API: POST /api/signup

Payload (JSON):

{
    "username": "<username>",
    "email": "<email>",
    "password": "<password>"
}


Response:

{"message": "User registered successfully!"}


Notes:

Display the message to the user.

If status code is 400, show error "Username already exists".

2. Login Page (login.html)

Button: Login

API: POST /api/login

Payload (JSON):

{
    "username": "<username>",
    "password": "<password>"
}


Response:

{"message": "Login successful"}   // or
{"message": "Wrong username or password"}


Notes:

On successful login, redirect to home.html.

Handle 401 errors to show wrong username/password.

3. Home Page (home.html)
Aadhaar Section

Upload/Extract Button

API: POST /api/extract

Form: multipart/form-data

Key: file → selected Aadhaar file

Response Example:

{
  "Name": "Hredhaan Naik",
  "DOB": "03-09-1981",
  "AadhaarNumber": "XXXX-XXXX-XXXX",
  "Gender": "Male",
  "Address": "29/592, Nagarajan Road, Ramagundam 879104"
}


Notes: Display extracted details on the page as preview section.

Save Button

API: POST /api/save

Payload (JSON): Use the extracted Aadhaar details

{
  "Name": "<Name>",
  "DOB": "<DOB>",
  "AadhaarNumber": "<AadhaarNumber>",
  "Gender": "<Gender>",
  "Address": "<Address>"
}


Response:

{"message": "Aadhaar details saved successfully!"}

PAN Section

Upload/Extract Button

API: POST /api/extract_pan

Form: multipart/form-data

Key: file → selected PAN file

Response Example:

{
  "Name": "Hredhaan Naik",
  "FatherName": "Parent Name",
  "PANNumber": "ABCDE1234F"
}


Notes: Display extracted details on the page.

Save Button

API: POST /api/save_pan

Payload (JSON): Use the extracted PAN details

{
  "Name": "<Name>",
  "FatherName": "<FatherName>",
  "PANNumber": "<PANNumber>"
}


Response:

{"message": "PAN details saved successfully!"}

4. Optional: Fetch Aadhaar Records

API: GET /api/record

Response: List of all Aadhaar records

[
  {
    "Name": "Hredhaan Naik",
    "DOB": "03-09-1981",
    "AadhaarNumber": "XXXX-XXXX-XXXX",
    "Gender": "Male",
    "Address": "29/592, Nagarajan Road, Ramagundam 879104"
  },
  ...
]

Frontend Notes

Always show success/error messages returned by the API.

Use fetch() or axios to call APIs from JavaScript.

For file uploads, use FormData() and append('file', file) to send files.
